<task type="auto">
  <name>Task 3: Add labels directly on phase regions</name>
  <files>quickice/output/phase_diagram.py</files>
  <action>
    Add phase labels (Ih, II, III, V, VI, VII, VIII) directly on each phase region, not just in legend.

    Use shapely to calculate the centroid of each polygon, then place the label there.

    Example:
    ```python
    from shapely.geometry import Polygon as ShapelyPolygon

    for phase_id, vertices in PHASE_POLYGONS.items():
        poly = ShapelyPolygon(vertices)
        centroid = poly.centroid
        label = PHASE_LABELS.get(phase_id, phase_id)
        ax.text(
            centroid.y, centroid.x,  # (P, T) -> (T, P) for display
            label,
            fontsize=12,
            fontweight='bold',
            ha='center',
            va='center',
            color='black',
            alpha=0.8,
        )
    ```
  </action>
