<task type="auto">
  <name>Task 5: Verify lookup-diagram consistency</name>
  <files>quickice/output/phase_diagram.py</files>
  <action>
    Create a verification script that tests consistency between lookup and diagram.

    Add a function to verify that a point's visual position on the diagram matches the lookup result:

    ```python
    def verify_consistency(T, P):
        '''Verify that diagram and lookup give same phase for a point.'''
        from quickice.phase_mapping.lookup import lookup_phase
        lookup_result = lookup_phase(T, P)

        # Check which polygon contains this point
        from shapely.geometry import Point
        from quickice.phase_mapping.data.ice_boundaries import PHASE_POLYGONS

        point = Point(T, P)
        diagram_phase = None
        for phase_id, vertices in PHASE_POLYGONS.items():
            from shapely.geometry import Polygon as ShapelyPolygon
            poly = ShapelyPolygon(vertices)
            if poly.covers(point):
                diagram_phase = phase_id
                break

        assert lookup_result == diagram_phase, f"Inconsistency at ({T}, {P}): lookup={lookup_result}, diagram={diagram_phase}"
        return True
    ```

    Run verification for several test points.
  </action>
  <verify>
    python -c "
# Test consistency at several points
from quickice.output.phase_diagram import verify_consistency

test_points = [
    (250, 500),    # Ice II or V
    (273, 0),      # Ice Ih
    (260, 300),    # Near II-III-V boundary
    (300, 2500),   # Ice VI
]

for T, P in test_points:
    try:
        verify_consistency(T, P)
        print(f'({T}K, {P}MPa) consistent ✓')
    except AssertionError as e:
        print(f'FAIL: {e}')
"
  </verify>
  <done>Lookup and diagram are consistent for all test points</done>
